        Is Aramid the Same as Carbon Fiber?
      </h3>
      <p class="{{descSize}} mb-12">
        Aramid fiber and carbon fiber are very different materials, each with their own
        useful properties. Even
        though carbon is often used to make phone cases as it is exceptionally lightweight and durable, it is also
        highly conductive, frequently blocking phone signals, which aramid does not. However, because of the
        conductivity of carbon fiber, it is an excellent RFID blocker, which is why we use it to make our MagEZ
        Wallets.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1  sm:grid-cols-3 gap-3 sm:gap-4 md:gap-6 auto-rows-fr ">
