            </picture>
            <p class="{{descSize}}">
              Carbon Fibre
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="{{descSize}}">
          A carbon (karbon) phone case, as its name implies, is made of carbon fibres instead of Aramid fibres. Carbon
          fibre is
          extremely strong in tension and compression and is by far the stiffest of the fibres. However, it is brittle.
          So
          the
          fibres aren't as tough as Aramid fibres. What does it mean to a phone case? A carbon(karbon) phone case will
          be
          also
          brittle of course. On the contrary, an Aramid phone case is more tough and flexible.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="w-full text-center">
        <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-color-white mb-6 font-bold">
          <span class="text-red-700 font-bold">02</span> Electrical Conductivity
